  "texts": [
    "For any policy π, we introduce two performance metrics by comparing it with the optimal policy π ⋆ as followsR-OPT(π):= | E x [ E y ∼ π [ r(x, y; π)] -E x [ E y ∼ π ⋆ [ r(x, y; π ⋆)] | U-OPT(π):= ∥ E x [ E y ∼ π [ h(x, y)]] -E x [ E y ∼ π ⋆ [ h(x, y)]] ∥ ∞where r(x, y; π):= r(x, y) -β log (π(y | x)/π ref (y | x)), and R-OPT(π) and U-OPT(π) quantify the optimality gap of the policy π regarding the reward and utility functions, respectively, in solving Problem (U-CA).",
    "In Algorithm 1, we readily obtain two policies from the Lagrangian maximization:π ⋆ p (• | x; λ) ∈ argmax θ ∈ Θ L(π θ, λ), by setting λ to λ = λ ⋆ and λ ⋆ p, respectively.",
    "We next establish that the two policies π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p) and π ⋆ p (λ ⋆) are both approximate solutions to Problem (U-CA).",
    "To proceed, we assume that the dual function is strongly convex at an optimal dual variable λ ⋆.",
    "It follows from Lemma 1."
